(10) Department means the
Bureau of Animal Industry of the Department of Agriculture with the State
Veterinarian in charge, subordinate only to the director;

(15) Inspector means any person
who is employed by the department and who is authorized to perform inspections
pursuant to the act;

(16) Licensee means a person
who has qualified for and received a license from the department pursuant
to the act;

(19) Premises means all public
or private buildings, kennels, pens, and cages used by a facility and the
public or private ground upon which a facility is located if such buildings,
kennels, pens, cages, or ground are used by the owner or operator of such
facility in the usual course of business;

(20) Primary enclosure means
any structure used to immediately restrict a dog or cat to a limited amount
of space, such as a room, pen, cage, or compartment;
